cs.CV, cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.IR 

This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) and natural language processing (cs.CL) sub-categories, as it deals with visual text recognition and aligning predicted strings with lexically valid strings. It also involves unsupervised learning, which could fall under machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper discusses the impact of varying the text corpus on recognition accuracy, which could relate to information retrieval (cs.IR).
